The paper deals with the capacity region of a multiple access channel with correlated sources, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses spectrum analysis, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper introduces a new data processing inequality, which is a concept in network information theory (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with upper bounds and necessary conditions, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
